caption: Tried this spot in the past with a friend and I am obsessed since then. I enjoy the great ambience and delightful dishes and beverages. Keep up the good work.
Great food and good service
Get there before noon, great lunch spot.
I pay for the food why are they giving such small portions as if they are giving it for free???? 14$ is not little for you guys to act as if you are giving free food? For sure I'm not going back

Staff is horrible if your not white. Literally had to wait for the conversation between the co workers to finish before I could order my food. Finally get there and the guy gives me attitude as if I’m in the wrong and then makes my food wrong after I told him what I wanted from the selection. Did NOT like the night staff on 12/6 before closing at 8:20pm. They were more concerned with cleaning up and breaking down the kitchen and talking about the manager imperfection as a manager to them instead of giving me what I asked for. The portions served to me were small and disrespectful especially paying for a $13 bowl. I will never eat at any digg in again and I highly suggest not to go there to the broad street location. I honestly love digg in and have been turned away from it due to this unpleasant experience. Just sharing my experience because I know digg in owners will not really do much to change this atmosphere provided by the people they hired here. So again don’t don’t don’t go to this location it’s gross in service form and it makes you feel like you waste your money just to go eat. Everyon that nite staff at 12/6 around 8:30 should be reviewed because it was Unwelcoming.

Absolutely love their food. When you go in and order they typically give you bigger portions. Service is provided with a smile!
Fresh and warm for with grains, greens and proteins

I work near this Dig Inn and the exhaust vent above this restaurant blows putrid fumes into the street all day, to the extent that it creates nasty stains on the sidewalk outside.  Everyone in my office knows exactly what I'm talking about and we even walk on the other side of the street to avoid the smell. It's absolutely disgusting, I am shocked they have not been shut down by the Health Department in fact.
Deliciously fresh food and very flavorful with very decent portion sizes. A lunch favorite amongst the office. Great for catering too.

Love love love Dig Inn. Healthy options, great veggies and variety. Love the pesto sauce. Totally try their cookies too. Yummmmm.
The price ranges from $11-15 but it's worth it. The food is fresh, tasty and really healthy

Walking in the place looks really well kept, and clean. I can really say I feel comfortable eating there. As how the place is arranged it seems really well though out. Not much place to sit but easy to get your lunch and keep moving fast out.  The price is $11-$15 dollars, healthy  motivated selections, reason why the long lines come around at lunch time. Order to pick up with dig-in makes it convenient  not to waste time on break, so that helps a lot.  TASTE! i have to say, really good! could not believe it because most places where they talk about eating good forget that it still has to taste good!  Lastly Category of foods are well done with selection of "protein". The have a few bases that you can base all your orders form, starting with classic brown rice, greens with mint , spiced farro  with butternut squash.  My favorite jasper hill Mac & Cheese as a Market side.
Not the prettiest picture but it all tasted really good and healthy. Good for the price.
stop cheaping out on your proteins... it's like a lottery at this place... 2 days out of the week, I get 4 pieces of herb roasted chicken. Like cmon...
Great place for a healthy lunch in a quick, clean environment.
Great go to lunch place 👌🏾 leave early before it gets crowded
Affordable, local, quick, delicious
The first place I've been to where it's credit card only while expensive the food was good.

Food is great
Delicious and seems to be healthy. Line goes very quick during lunch 'rush' hours. Prices for  are $11-$14 based on protein selection
Very tasty and quick wholesome food. perfect for a quick lunch bite and much healthier than fast food equivalent
I guess it's healthy but the food tastes like cardboard.
Really like the bases and variety of sides. I always feel guilty but I always get the Mac and cheese which is delicious.
Fresh and good. Sweet pototoes and kale salad were really good.
Delicious. Affordable. Healthy. Long line moves fast even at lunch.
This was after I microwaved the meat.

(Translated by Google) A chain of restaurants to try if you are fond of new concepts. You compose your own bowls by adding a base such as rice or quinoa as well as accompaniments (baked carrots, broccoli, Mac & cheese, sweet potatoes ...). I ate here twice while in New York: delicious!  (Original) Une chaîne de restaurants à tester si vous êtes friands des nouveaux concepts. Vous composer vous-même vos bols en y ajoutant une base tel que du riz ou du quinoa ainsi que des accompagnements (carottes au four, brocolis, Mac&cheese, patates douces...). J’y ai mangé deux fois lors ce que j’étais à New York : un délice !

There's usually a line out the door around lunchtime, but it's because the food is so good and the staff is so friendly.   Love the seasonal menu changes and the food is always delicious (hooray the return of brussels sprouts!).   Definitely on the more expensive side for lunch ($14 for salmon, two sides, and a base), but it's quality ingredients and healthy.  Never been disappointed and I've eaten here more times than I care to admit.   Empress is the NICEST CASHIER ever--she always has a compliment for everyone and radiates positive energy.
Heavy in my lunch rotation. Good quality food and happy employees.

We were trying to find somewhere healthy to have a quick lunch. Stumbled across Dig Inn and was so pleasantly surprised! Delicious. Customer service from the servers could be a lot better. The cashier was fab though, really lovely and complimented us as we walked in!

Will be great if they can put the menu on top of the counter, atleast won't be a guessing game to figure out how it works. That being said you can choose between 2 or 3 sides and meat with a base of rice or salad. Food is ok, portions are on a smaller side and relatively expensive.
Healthy food choices with no salt.
Good food.
Grab and go home style cooking, satisfies every time.
Always fresh, locally sourced,  delicious with a great variety of vegetables.

I live near by so I come by here all the time for lunch. I’ve been to dig inns around the city and this is the best one I have ever been to. They’re professional, hard working and very friendly and welcoming. I’m always in a good mood when I leave this location. Please consider adding a tip jar! Your employees are awesome!! Each and every one of them always have a smile to their face.
Delicious mix &match salads with great produce and a sustainability focus. It can get pricey and easily cost $12 for a bowl!
The food here is great. I myself am a fan of their chicken and kale. Very healthy options and clean environment

It’s tasty, albeit seriously overpriced for what it is, but unfortunately not unusual for the area. Ordering online is absolutely the way to go. In a recent trip I saw a line out the door, but the food is ordered online an hour before was ready to go, perhaps a bit cooler than if I’d preferred it in real time. The proteins are high quality and amazingly the steak isn’t over cooked. The salmon didn’t look great to me but I haven’t tasted it. The quinoa is fine. The drinks are pretty good, certainly a step above average, nicely flavored lemonade and teas, appropriately sweet, and surprisingly good value compared to competitors, although of course lemon juice and tea are not expensive so they still get a great markup on their end. The staff were friendly and patient with newcomers. And with a line out the door, the place is probably doing something right. There’s not a ton of seating but I haven’t dined in so I don’t know what turnover is like.
Really enjoyed the food. Make your own bowl. My wild caught salmon was surprisingly moist and  seasoned.    I enjoyed meeting Empress. Her wonderful personality made eating at Dig Inn a delight.

Food was tasty, but servings were a but smaller than what I get at the Brookfield mall Hudson Eats location and they did not have little signs to show what the options were. We enjoyed the citrus golden beets, chicken breast, kale salad (salty though). There is only one high chair, and you may need to wipe it down (it's a bit grubby).
Good food but poor training for employees
The food was great
The only bad part is the line....
Great place for lunch in FiDi. High quality home cooked meals with real substance.
Healthy food for affordable prices. Not to mention the food is delicious. The staff are very kind, attentive, and knowledge about the menu.
Love the chicken here

First off, the facility is nice and kept clean. Next the safe is welcoming and very pleasant to talk to. The food there is amazing. Their menu is regularly changing to keep up with what is being demanded. They also do delivery.

Good food but inconsistent portions. Seats here are also arranged terribly. One side of the tables are completely smothered by the line waiting to order. Also door stays open so it's super cold by the entrance if you sit there.
Great brussel sprouts

This used to be my go-to lunch spot when I was feeling something healthy. DigInn has a reputation of using some of the freshest ingredients.  The food is good and healthy, but the portions got a lot smaller while the price kept increasing.

Dig Inn is one of the best counter-serve places to get lunch from in FiDi. You can pick what base, vegetables and meat you want in a "Chipotle" counter style. You can expect to pay about $10-15 for a bowl, but the food tastes so fresh and good and flavorful, that the price seems quite reasonable. Besides, that's a similar range to what you'd find at other counter serve lunch places. The ingredients are locally sourced and change seasonally, but you certainly don't have to care whether your food comes from local sources to simply appreciate how good the food tastes here.
Hot diet-friendly food
Food is so good here. Line is long but moves really fast.
It's usually crowded up until 1:45, but it's good filling food. Staff here are nice.
The food wasn't cooked enough and it tasted weird, plus the customer service was horrible. I wouln't go again.

Good lunch place. A lot of options (hot/cold, vegetables/meat) and everything looked amazing. Be aware of the very long line during lunch hour. So there is enough time to think about what you want, but you feel being rushed when you are ordering. The price is ok (if you compare it to the salad bar of Wholefoods or Essen).
A great place  to have a vegetarian  meal, fish and meat available  if that is your  preference .
Crowded.
Love the food in here. Don't miss the sweet potato. It's delicious.

Great food! I love their options. Hot foods, cold foods, protein/meat all great options. Its hard to disappoint but on the pricey side though.  Lately they got rid of the food menu and we no longer see a Menu anywhere nor labels in front of the food items. On top of that, they're always rushing because of the lines. Could improve in that aspect I guess.

Excellent food.
One of my new favorite farm to table healthy options. It's a fair quantity for a fair price. Also much more sustainable than the other lunch options!
Love this place! Healthy and delicious, at an affordable price!

The food is ok but they are always out of something that you want.  Also, the service is terrible.  Don't expect a hello from any of the people working.  In fact, the lady taking money at the register was so busy gossiping with her friend that she didn't even acknowledge me when I was paying, didn't look up at me once.  I asked for a bag several times, on the 3rd attempt at asking for a bag, she looked up at me and said "I heard you" and im sitting there wondering why you didn't acknowledge the fact that I am speaking to you and making a very simple request.  There are places near here that serve better food and don't treat you like an inconvenience when you eat there.
Great options for everyone.  Really enjoyed my food.

The food was unreal. The pace of the employees was great! However, they should have menus at the front because the customer will know what it wants and it will make the line go faster.

The food here is amazing! The lines can be intimidating during peak lunch hours, but it goes by quick.  The best time to get your food is around 12:30 pm. That is when the food is super fresh.  I was pretty annoyed when they drastically raised the prices and didn't increase the portions, but other than that, this has been my go-to spot for lunch.

The worst staff ever. They are rude, even to customers that visit frequently.

The food at Dig Inn is amazing. Delicious, healthy and surprisingly reasonable in its price. This particular location is more spacious than their sister post on Broad St. Still, gets very crowded during noon on weekdays.

Love this place and go there all the time!  They have a nice selection of vegetarian hot and cold selections (mac and cheese and the sweet potatoes are my favorite), beef, chicken, salmon (particularly good) and a meatball offering as well.  The evening manager Johely along with her servers Aqua and Diyanni make me feel very welcome!  I'm lactose intolerant plus I have a food intolerance for a lot of food additives as well, so the healthy "clean" meals really 'hits the spot' when working a late shift.  Along with a really nice price point (especially for the downtown Wallstreet area) of $6.50 - $12.00 or so for the combination plates, it can't be beat!
Average lukewarm tasty food.  The small is like a happy meal.
Healthy food on the heart of wall Street
